&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic Staff Nurses to work as part of the Integrated Health and Social Care Team based within North Lincolnshire Community Services, and although based in one locality it will be expected you will work from any Community base if required. This is a fixed term contract from November 2020 to September 2021.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Community Staff Nurses are an integral part of the District Nursing team providing skilled nursing care to patients in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To assist with the assessment of care needs the development of care programmes and the implementation and evaluation of care. To carry out unsupervised delegated nursing duties, and to be an effective member of the network, developing and maintaining effective channels of communication with other professionals and agencies. Supervise and support unqualified staff, and act as mentor for pre-registration students.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must be flexible, caring, and professional and have the ability to remain calm under pressure. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We expect you to provide advice and information to patients and their carers as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Birchall, Team Leader South Network&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address r.birchall@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
